name: The Hadal Snailfish
description:
Snailfishes are the deepest living fishes and have been observed down to more than 8000 m. In 2010 this image was taken at 7050 m/23,130 ft depth in the Atacama Trench (West coast of South America). It has been replicated countless times as art, in scientific publications and even in The Blue Planet books and posters. It is the first Google image hit for Hadal Snailfish. Despite its viral fame, this remains an unknown species and is likely even an unknown genus.

While the image is found everywhere online, this is the never released unedited raw data as it came from the lander vehicle. Minted by the scientists who took it.

The verified owners of this NFT are entitled to ‘behind the scenes’ media about the find which has never been released. 
As well as the above, the first to purchase this NFT will be invited to an in-person experience to be arranged based on their geographical location.
 
To claim contact: info@armatusoceanic.com
